295
00:20:14,692 --> 00:20:16,644
Oh, I thought you don't care.

296
00:20:17,445 --> 00:20:23,543
Wear something that makes you look like
the sexy bad boy you really are.

297
00:20:23,644 --> 00:20:25,782
Something that makes Mister Wife and Kids

298
00:20:25,783 --> 00:20:28,265
question all of his middle-class choices.

299
00:20:28,266 --> 00:20:30,860
I'm all for that, just as long as you wear something low-cut in the back,

300
00:20:30,861 --> 00:20:34,019
so he can see my name branded on your ass!

301
00:20:58,197 --> 00:21:00,238
Hello! Hello?

302
00:21:04,782 --> 00:21:06,614
Hello?

303
00:21:17,213 --> 00:21:18,734
Hello?

304
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,862
Hey. New casket wall, huh?

305
00:21:24,863 --> 00:21:27,710
You boys are doing better than I thought.

306
00:21:28,268 --> 00:21:30,014
I'm Mitzi Dalton Huntley.

307
00:21:30,015 --> 00:21:31,580
David Fisher.

308
00:21:33,776 --> 00:21:36,377
Do you need to plan a funeral?

309
00:21:38,697 --> 00:21:41,653
You have no idea who I am do you.

310
00:21:42,317 --> 00:21:46,768
I'm Southwest Regional Director
for Kroehner Services, International.

311
00:21:46,869 --> 00:21:52,550
I was hoping that maybe you and your brother
might share a cup of coffee with me.

312
00:22:00,732 --> 00:22:05,173
Well, hello!
Mitzi Dalton Huntley.

313
00:22:05,474 --> 00:22:07,382
Nate Fisher.

314
00:22:08,965 --> 00:22:11,074
You're a runner, huh?

315
00:22:11,727 --> 00:22:13,746
It's bad for your knees.

316
00:22:13,747 --> 00:22:15,692
Yeah, well, everything's bad for something.

317
00:22:15,693 --> 00:22:17,797
So I hear.

318
00:22:19,134 --> 00:22:20,700
Why are you here?

319
00:22:20,943 --> 00:22:24,099
