359
00:24:27,244 --> 00:24:29,192
Don't ever say that again!

360
00:24:29,493 --> 00:24:31,331
Very nice.

361
00:24:31,332 --> 00:24:35,319
Oh, welcome to Casketeria!
May I take your order?

362
00:24:37,052 --> 00:24:39,860
So, Mr. Langmead is all ready to go.

363
00:24:39,861 --> 00:24:41,501
Great.

364
00:24:42,998 --> 00:24:47,478
Yeah. So, Nate, have you guys had a chance
to think about what we...you know?

365
00:24:47,824 --> 00:24:49,316
- Uh, yeah...
- yeah?

366
00:24:49,317 --> 00:24:52,071
- Yeah, let's go in the office.
- Okay.

367
00:24:58,817 --> 00:25:01,910
So do these really open?
Can you, like, hide shit in here?

368
00:25:02,411 --> 00:25:04,010
Can you close the door?

369
00:25:06,739 --> 00:25:09,020
Close the door doesn't sound too good.

370
00:25:13,667 --> 00:25:16,347
We can't give you a loan right now, Rico.

371
00:25:17,178 --> 00:25:20,556
Look, we just spent a fortune
on the new casket wall,

372
00:25:20,557 --> 00:25:22,407
and now we have to maintain an emergency fund

373
00:25:22,408 --> 00:25:26,444
in case Kroehner starts acting up again,
which suddenly looks very likely.

374
00:25:27,396 --> 00:25:29,753
It was a tough choice, I'm sorry.

375
00:25:31,158 --> 00:25:33,537
How much did that casket wall cost?

376
00:25:36,604 --> 00:25:39,242
Rico, our first priority is
keeping this house open.

377
00:25:39,243 --> 00:25:40,832
The more income we make, the more you can make.

378
00:25:40,833 --> 00:25:45,853
Tell me one thing. Did you and David decide to buy that wall
before or after we spoke.

379
00:25:51,975 --> 00:25:55,214
Wow. You know, first you won't make me a partner,
now you won't even...

380
00:25:55,215 --> 00:25:57,994
God, you know, I've had it with you moping
about not being a partner.

381
00:25:57,995 --> 00:25:59,460
It's not happening, alright?

382
00:25:59,461 --> 00:26:02,126
I wish I could help you, but I can't.

383
00:26:02,127 --> 00:26:07,723
I mean, fuck, we're your employer, alright!
We're not a goddamned savings and loan!

384
00:26:12,702 --> 00:26:14,623
I'm sorry, Rico.

385
00:26:16,387 --> 00:26:19,592
If it were my money,
I'd give you all of it, you know that.

386
00:26:19,807 --> 00:26:29,238
Yeah. Yeah, yeah. I'll pass it along to my kids,
after playing in a parking lot next to a dumpster!

387
00:26:37,363 --> 00:26:38,911
Fuck!

388
00:27:03,325 --> 00:27:05,492
I'm scared.

389
00:27:07,132 --> 00:27:09,210
What's gonna happen to me now?

390
00:27:09,211 --> 00:27:11,516
Well, that''s not my problem, pal.

391
00:27:18,122 --> 00:27:19,388
What?

392
00:27:19,389 --> 00:27:21,587
I was so young.

393
00:27:22,102 --> 00:27:23,417
Why me?

394
00:27:23,418 --> 00:27:26,497
Well, why the fuck not you? What?
Did you think you were immune to this?

395
00:27:26,498 --> 00:27:28,903
Everybody!

396
00:27:28,904 --> 00:27:32,155
What makes you so fuckin' special?

397
00:27:45,379 --> 00:27:47,020
What do you think?

398
00:27:47,021 --> 00:27:49,230
I'm not signing up for anything.

399
00:27:49,431 --> 00:27:53,931
Oh, I'm not selling anything.
I'm a visitor, just like you.

400
00:27:54,837 --> 00:27:59,001
Do you know how you can tell?
The Elevated wear plastic tags.

401
00:27:59,002 --> 00:28:00,353
The Elevated?

402
00:28:00,354 --> 00:28:02,196
Oh, you'll learn the lingo.

403
00:28:02,197 --> 00:28:05,944
My daughter is graduating today.
You?

404
00:28:05,945 --> 00:28:08,785
My business associate is graduating.

405
00:28:09,306 --> 00:28:11,018
So what exactly is this?

406
00:28:11,019 --> 00:28:13,814
Well, I don't know for sure myself.

407
00:28:13,815 --> 00:28:16,686
But Shelia has never been happier,

408
00:28:16,687 --> 00:28:19,705
so I wanted to see what it was all about.

409
00:28:19,706 --> 00:28:21,674
<i>Let's get started.</i>

410
00:28:21,675 --> 00:28:25,295
<i>Today just might be the most important day
of your entire lives.</i>

411
00:28:25,396 --> 00:28:28,986
Come sit with me.
There's safety in numbers.

412
00:28:31,090 --> 00:28:36,560
You cannot design a life that works
without first drafting a clear blueprint.

413
00:28:36,861 --> 00:28:43,672
And you cannot construct a life that has meaning
without first laying a solid foundation.

414
00:28:43,673 --> 00:28:47,603
You are the architect of your life.

415
00:28:47,604 --> 00:28:50,295
Not your emotionally distant father.

416
00:28:50,396 --> 00:28:53,209
Not your overly critical mother.

417
00:28:53,510 --> 00:28:56,864
Not your petty, fairweather friends.

418
00:28:58,001 --> 00:28:59,205
You !

419
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:11,892
It was hard the first time I stood up for myself.

420
00:29:12,745 --> 00:29:15,813
I always wanted everybody to like me.

421
00:29:16,066 --> 00:29:19,890
Even though I hated myself, you had to like me.

422
00:29:19,891 --> 00:29:22,316
When I rebuilt my foundation,

423
00:29:22,917 --> 00:29:27,200
and I was able to honor
and elevate the better part of me,

424
00:29:27,201 --> 00:29:30,481
I realized I really like me.

425
00:29:31,425 --> 00:29:33,631
So you don't have to!

426
00:29:37,849 --> 00:29:40,631
I'm not a salvage job.

427
00:29:40,632 --> 00:29:43,877
I am not a teardown.
I am not junk.

428
00:29:44,852 --> 00:29:49,107
It's taken me many years to say that.
To believe it.

429
00:29:49,384 --> 00:29:53,990
