00:34:05,554 --> 00:34:10,440
Wow, Bren, it's great to see you!
It really is.

490
00:34:10,441 --> 00:34:14,332
Oh my God! I'm gonna cry!

491
00:34:14,998 --> 00:34:18,425
- You must be Dawn!
- Hi! Oh, it's nice to meet you.

492
00:34:18,426 --> 00:34:22,362
Thank you so much for letting us bring Will.
Trevor really wanted you to meet him.

493
00:34:23,011 --> 00:34:24,967
Oh, I really wanted to meet him.

494
00:34:26,068 --> 00:34:27,568
Hey, hi, Will!

495
00:34:28,269 --> 00:34:30,356
Will, can you say hi?

496
00:34:30,357 --> 00:34:32,256
He'll crash in a little while. I promise.

497
00:34:32,257 --> 00:34:34,648
- Hi. I'm Trevor.
- Nate.

498
00:34:34,649 --> 00:34:35,966
Oh! Nate. Dawn.

499
00:34:35,967 --> 00:34:37,159
- Hi. How are you?
- Pleasure.

500
00:34:37,160 --> 00:34:39,222


501
00:34:40,248 --> 00:34:43,148
This place is really cool.

502
00:34:46,447 --> 00:34:49,025
- Yeah. So, wine anyone?
- I'd love a glass.

503
00:34:49,226 --> 00:34:50,263
...

504
00:34:50,264 --> 00:34:51,534
<i>I want wine!</i>

505
00:34:51,535 --> 00:34:55,829
Oh, you do? Well, what do you say?

506
00:34:56,430 --> 00:34:59,235
<i>Hi, Mr. Pooh Bear. Do you remember
what we discussed in the car?</i>

507
00:34:59,236 --> 00:35:02,132
....

508
00:35:03,641 --> 00:35:05,582
"I want wine, please!"

509
00:35:05,683 --> 00:35:06,800
Please

510
00:35:06,801 --> 00:35:09,576
So, how's the press tour going?

511
00:35:09,577 --> 00:35:14,708
Oh, God, I feel like such a sell-out!
I actually did "Politically Incorrect" last night!

512
00:35:14,709 --> 00:35:16,144
Wow! Was it fun?

513
00:35:16,145 --> 00:35:19,006
Oh, hardly. It was me, Kobe Bryant,

514
00:35:19,007 --> 00:35:22,826
that emaciated chick from "The Practice,"
and some twelve year old rap singer

515
00:35:22,827 --> 00:35:24,950
I'd never even heard of!

516
00:35:25,881 --> 00:35:29,051
I read your first book.
I thought it was brilliant.

517
00:35:29,052 --> 00:35:30,415
Thank you!

518
00:35:30,416 --> 00:35:34,563
- I can send you a copy of the new one, if you'd like.
- I would. Thank you.

519
00:35:34,564 --> 00:35:37,289
You know, I read "Charlotte: Light and Dark."

520
00:35:37,650 --> 00:35:40,514
Oh, dear! Why?

521
00:35:40,515 --> 00:35:43,950
In grad school. I had this idiot
professor who insisted

522
00:35:43,951 --> 00:35:48,712
that it was the perfect profile of
a classic borderline personality.

523
00:35:49,723 --> 00:35:51,923
You've heard that before, right?

524
00:35:52,024 --> 00:35:55,122
I actually went to the library,
looked up the symptoms

525
00:35:55,123 --> 00:35:57,655
and started behaving like that
just to fuck with them!

526
00:35:57,656 --> 00:35:59,191
Seriously?

527
00:35:59,617 --> 00:36:02,585
That's brilliant!
How old were you?

528
00:36:02,786 --> 00:36:06,416
I must have been 9 or 10.
It was towards the end.

529
00:36:06,717 --> 00:36:08,686
Personally, I think it's a crock of shit.

530
00:36:08,687 --> 00:36:11,684
Did you ever notice how the majority
of borderlines are women?

531
00:36:11,685 --> 00:36:15,712
I see it as just a misogynistic
attempt to pathologize women

532
00:36:15,713 --> 00:36:18,606
who refuse to toe the patriarchal line!

533
00:36:19,766 --> 00:36:24,466
Yeah, yeah, I spent 6 months in Seattle
on a teaching fellowship.

534
00:36:24,467 --> 00:36:25,655
Ever do any cliimbing up there?

535
00:36:25,656 --> 00:36:29,926
Oh, yeah, some boulder climbing.
Normal climbing with ropes but...

536
00:36:29,927 --> 00:36:31,698
Are you a cragger?

537
00:36:32,366 --> 00:36:35,619
Eh. Rank amateur urban kind, but I love it.

538
00:36:35,899 --> 00:36:37,724
You done climbing rock?

539
00:36:37,725 --> 00:36:42,161
Yeah, that's where I learned.
I never knew 30 feet was so high off the ground.

540
00:36:42,362 --> 00:36:44,030
30 feet? That's nothing!

541
00:36:44,031 --> 00:36:46,871
I've got a couple of buddies.
They're real thrillseekers.

542
00:36:46,872 --> 00:36:48,221
I mean, they climb high,

543
00:36:48,222 --> 00:36:51,184
but no way I can do that.

544
00:36:52,750 --> 00:36:55,743
Gotta think about more than just myself now.

545
00:37:01,543 --> 00:37:03,631
Bren looks great.

546
00:37:04,879 --> 00:37:06,528
How's she doing?

547
00:37:06,729 --> 00:37:08,534
Oh, she's doing great.

548
00:37:08,535 --> 00:37:11,344
- Man, she is so fucking smart!
- Yes, she is!

549
00:37:11,345 --> 00:37:15,106
She used to run circles around me,
I can tell you that.

550
00:37:15,607 --> 00:37:18,976
Everybody expected such great things from her.
551
00:37:21,864 --> 00:37:23,915
How's her brother?

551
00:37:25,693 --> 00:37:28,596
He's in the hospital
right now.

552
00:37:41,614 --> 00:37:44,025
I just really wanted to get out of my head,

553
00:37:44,026 --> 00:37:47,712
so I took 18 months of classes,
down at the Shiatsu Institute,

554
00:37:47,713 --> 00:37:51,358
thinking I'd do it until I figured out
what I really wanted to do.

555
00:37:51,359 --> 00:37:54,278
And here we are 10 years later.

556
00:37:54,279 --> 00:37:56,393
- But you love what you do, right?
- I do.

557
00:37:56,394 --> 00:37:58,678
That's the key.
And you know what?

558
00:37:58,679 --> 00:38:02,241
There is this girl in my health club.
She doesn't do shiatsu,

559
00:38:02,242 --> 00:38:06,238
but I swear. She is gifted.
Gif-ted!

560
00:38:06,839 --> 00:38:09,334
You know, there's a science to shiatsu.

561
00:38:09,335 --> 00:38:12,777
Chinese medicine dates back over 2000 years.

562
00:38:16,538 --> 00:38:19,688
Hmm...This is delicious, Brenda.
You know, I never cook like this.

563
00:38:19,689 --> 00:38:21,969
I can make pasta, but that's about it.

564
00:38:21,970 --> 00:38:26,048
She's got me beat. I can make toast.
And ice cubes.

565
00:38:26,049 --> 00:38:28,640
Nate does pretty good microwave popcorn.

566
00:38:28,741 --> 00:38:30,871
What do you do, Nate?

567
00:38:31,508 --> 00:38:33,826
I'm a funeral director.

568
00:38:35,713 --> 00:38:36,946
Really?

569
00:38:40,111 --> 00:38:45,473
What--what--what makes one to decide to--uh--
become a funeral director?

570
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:49,115
Well, I was born into it, actually.

571
00:38:50,090 --> 00:38:52,703
Sort of like being born into the Mafia.

572
00:39:01,852 --> 00:39:05,313
Hey, not so fast there, hotshot!
It's a tow road!

573
00:39:26,683 --> 00:39:29,084
Will ! Will !

574
00:39:29,085 --> 00:39:30,384
Time out.

575
00:39:30,385 --> 00:39:34,637
Sometimes he becomes completely irrational
just to gain attention.

576
00:39:34,838 --> 00:39:37,865
Hell, sometimes I do that.

577
00:39:46,635 --> 00:39:47,903
Oncle K !

578
00:39:48,004 --> 00:39:50,972
Hey, baby girl!
Happy birthday!

579
00:39:51,173 --> 00:39:52,508
I'm 9.

580
00:39:52,709 --> 00:39:55,121
Oh, well, I guess that means
I can't call you "Baby Girl" anymore.

581
00:39:55,222 --> 00:39:56,790
You better not!

582
00:39:57,391 --> 00:39:58,889
This is my friend, David.

583
00:39:58,890 --> 00:40:01,281
- Hi, there.
- Hi.

584
00:40:01,282 --> 00:40:03,367
So where's the party?

585
00:40:22,202 --> 00:40:24,370
You want some? It's good.

586
00:40:25,966 --> 00:40:28,024
This is for you, sweetheart.

587
00:40:35,012 --> 00:40:36,567
I saw this in the store!

588
00:40:36,568 --> 00:40:38,939
Yeah, I can't believe they still make these!

589
00:40:38,940 --> 00:40:42,561
- I thought you'd like it.
- Thanks, Uncle K.

590
00:40:46,144 --> 00:40:49,265
- Where's Mommy?
- In the bedroom, sleeping.

591
00:40:50,266 --> 00:40:54,225
- I'm going to go and talk to her for a little bit, alright?
- Okay.

592
00:41:13,269 --> 00:41:14,562
Carla !

593
00:41:21,094 --> 00:41:22,301
Carla !

594
00:41:28,588 --> 00:41:30,045
Hi...

595
00:41:30,146 --> 00:41:32,221
Thought you wasn't comin' till later.

596
00:41:32,322 --> 00:41:36,136
It is later.
What happened to Taylor's birthday party?

597
00:41:36,934 --> 00:41:38,945
Shit!

598
00:41:39,335 --> 00:41:42,476
I got home from work and was bone-tired.

599
00:41:42,477 --> 00:41:45,822
I'll take her to the flea market on the weekend,
get her something.

600
00:41:45,823 --> 00:41:47,260
That's all you did for her birthday?

601
00:41:47,261 --> 00:41:48,883
Buy her an Entennmann's cake?!?

602
00:41:48,984 --> 00:41:50,579
It's her favorite.

603
00:41:55,960 --> 00:41:57,225
What are you on?

604
00:41:57,226 --> 00:41:59,914
- Don't lie to me!
- I ain't on nothin'! Ok?

605
00:41:59,915 --> 00:42:02,138
What? You think I'm suicidal or
just plain stupid?

606
00:42:02,139 --> 00:42:06,266
I think you need to stop living just for yourself,
and start thinking about that little girl in there.

607
00:42:06,267 --> 00:42:10,233
I am 7 months clean! I work 2 jobs
and take care of my kid!

608
00:42:10,234 --> 00:42:13,516
What? I forgot her motherfuckin' birthday!
Do you want to arrest me for that?

609
00:42:13,517 --> 00:42:16,759
Look, you can do all the damage you want to yourself.
I can't stop that.

610
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:19,682
But I'm not gonna let you fuck up her life!

611
00:42:19,883 --> 00:42:21,456
- Take your hands off me.
- Carla...

612
00:42:21,457 --> 00:42:25,548
I will file an assault charge,
and you do not want that.

613
00:42:30,740 --> 00:42:33,498
My sister had one of these when she was a kid.

614
00:42:33,499 --> 00:42:34,802
But I broke it.

615
00:42:34,903 --> 00:42:36,392
On purpose?

616
00:42:36,393 --> 00:42:39,678
No. I wanted to make a pizza,

617
00:42:39,679 --> 00:42:43,480
and I put in a 300 watt bulb,
and the whole thing melted!

618
00:42:43,581 --> 00:42:45,122
That's dumb!

619
00:42:45,223 --> 00:42:47,447
Yeah, I know, and I was 17.

620
00:42:48,648 --> 00:42:52,985
<i>You don't give a fuck about her!
I'm talkin' to you!</i>

621
00:42:52,986 --> 00:42:55,310
<i>You don't know shit!
Get the fuck out of my house!</i>

622
00:42:55,311 --> 00:42:57,047
<i>I do! I do!</i>

623
00:42:57,048 --> 00:43:01,000
- Do you live in a house?
- Yup.

624
00:43:01,101 --> 00:43:02,835
A big house?

625
00:43:02,836 --> 00:43:04,720
Not that big.

626
00:43:06,788 --> 00:43:08,666
Got a daddy?

627
00:43:09,677 --> 00:43:11,443
I used to.

628
00:43:18,492 --> 00:43:20,859
- We gotta go, okay?
- Okay.

629
00:43:20,860 --> 00:43:22,417
Alright, listen, uh...

630
00:43:23,210 --> 00:43:24,827
I'll come back tomorrow

631
00:43:24,828 --> 00:43:28,063
as soon as I get off work,
and we'll go to the movies, okay?

632
00:43:28,164 --> 00:43:29,809
Okay.

633
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,286
We gotta go.

634
00:43:50,162 --> 00:43:51,737
Oh, my God!

635
00:43:52,228 --> 00:43:54,412
What was I thinking?

636
00:43:54,713 --> 00:43:57,797
Well, I was only 19.

637
00:43:57,798 --> 00:44:00,127
Aw, come on, it wasn't that bad.

638
00:44:00,614 --> 00:44:05,448
"There's this girl at my health club.
She is gif-ted!

639
00:44:05,449 --> 00:44:07,157
Gif-ted".

640
00:44:07,158 --> 00:44:08,766
What a dork!

641
00:44:08,767 --> 00:44:11,104
His ears were filthy.
Did you notice that?

642
00:44:11,105 --> 00:44:12,289
No.

643
00:44:12,390 --> 00:44:13,792
Now, her I liked.

644
00:44:13,793 --> 00:44:16,094
That kid! What a freak!

645
00:44:17,091 --> 00:44:19,687
tart saving up for therapy now!

646
00:44:20,680 --> 00:44:24,341
We need some friends.
Some couples we don't hate.

647
00:44:24,478 --> 00:44:26,488
We have each other.

648
00:44:30,121 --> 00:44:33,303
Maybe we should volunteer some place.

649
00:44:33,952 --> 00:44:36,131
No, I'm serious.

650
00:44:36,868 --> 00:44:39,294
Do something good for the world.

651
00:44:39,461 --> 00:44:42,174
Exchange Program.

652
00:44:42,611 --> 00:44:46,150
Habitat for Humanity. Meels on Wheels.

653
00:44:46,551 --> 00:44:49,558
Just give more, consume less.

654
00:44:50,859 --> 00:44:52,824
Brenda, I'm dying.

655
00:44:52,925 --> 00:44:56,871
What? What did you say?

656
00:44:56,872 --> 00:45:02,911
After the auto accident, I had x-rays, MRIs,
and they found something.

657
00:45:03,834 --> 00:45:08,822
They found... it's called AVM, I don't know.
And I think I'm gonna die from it. I don't know when.

658
00:45:12,748 --> 00:45:15,316
I'm so scared.

659
00:45:20,744 --> 00:45:22,602
Are you listening to me?

660
00:45:22,603 --> 00:45:23,778
Yeah.

661
00:45:24,371 --> 00:45:26,437
Meels on Wheels.

662
00:45:27,337 --> 00:45:29,122
You really wanna do that?

663
00:45:29,523 --> 00:45:32,260
I don't know. I have to do something.

664
00:45:32,461 --> 00:45:35,097
I hate my fucking life.

665
00:45:35,098 --> 00:45:36,939
What's wrong?

666
00:45:36,940 --> 00:45:40,271
I was watching Trevor and Dawn tonight,

667
00:45:41,444 --> 00:45:47,145
thinking...
they're just so...so complete.

668
00:45:47,551 --> 00:45:51,682
Like they have something
that I will never have, ever.

669
00:45:51,683 --> 00:45:55,416
Either I wasn't born with it,
or it was beaten out of me,

670
00:45:55,417 --> 00:45:57,579
or maybe,

671
00:45:57,580 --> 00:45:59,630
maybe I made myself into a self-fulfilling prophecy,

672
00:45:59,631 --> 00:46:01,485
and I really am a borderline personality.

673
00:46:01,486 --> 00:46:03,975
Now, wouldn't that be ironic?

674
00:46:05,413 --> 00:46:07,367
Hey, what's going on with you?

675
00:46:09,727 --> 00:46:11,431
Je ne sais pas.

676
00:46:12,501 --> 00:46:15,413
I don't know. I spent my childhood performing
for clinicians,

677
00:46:15,414 --> 00:46:18,347
the rest of my life taking care of my trainwreck
of a brother,

678
00:46:18,348 --> 00:46:22,187
and I have no idea who I am.

679
00:46:25,547 --> 00:46:28,365
I'm gonna make a cup of tea.
Want one?

680
00:46:30,095 --> 00:46:31,889
No thanks.

681
00:46:42,506 --> 00:46:45,910
God, I can't wait until our next funeral!

682
00:46:46,011 --> 00:46:48,038
What do you think, Mom?

683
00:46:48,039 --> 00:46:50,164
It's very modern.

684
00:46:50,165 --> 00:46:53,275
We figure it'll pay for itself in less than 8 months.

685
00:46:53,276 --> 00:46:55,669
What did we spend on this?

686
00:46:57,397 --> 00:46:59,409
About 20000 $.

687
00:47:00,438 --> 00:47:03,644
How much is left in the reserve fund
I gave you?

688
00:47:03,645 --> 00:47:05,026
I'll have to check.

689
00:47:05,027 --> 00:47:08,199
I want a full accounting of how you spent that 93000 $.

690
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:13,092
I'm an investor in Fisher & Sons.
That wall is part of my investment, and I want a return!

691
00:47:13,093 --> 00:47:14,280
Well, of course, Mom.

692
00:47:14,281 --> 00:47:17,898
I am speaking fiercely from the Eye!

693
00:47:18,099 --> 00:47:20,143
Do you mind?

694
00:47:24,089 --> 00:47:25,740
I don't know.

695
00:47:25,741 --> 00:47:28,054
I just need one of you to sign right here,

696
00:47:28,055 --> 00:47:29,543
and we'll be done

697
00:47:29,998 --> 00:47:33,366
Do we need to write you a check right now,
or can we just mail it to your office?

698
00:47:33,567 --> 00:47:36,210
Uh, you might want to open this first.

699
00:47:37,541 --> 00:47:39,387
It's beautiful.

700
00:47:39,388 --> 00:47:41,463
- It's great.
- It's great.

701
00:47:45,674 --> 00:47:50,683
"Enjoy the new casket wall. It's on me.
Kisses. Mitzi Dalton Huntley.".

702
00:47:51,084 --> 00:47:52,819
Why would she pay for our wall?

703
00:47:52,820 --> 00:47:56,608
She didn't pay for it.
Appleby Caskets is owned by Kroehner.

704
00:47:57,182 --> 00:47:58,368
Since when?

705
00:47:58,369 --> 00:48:00,397
Since three weeks ago.

706
00:48:00,851 --> 00:48:02,446
Enjoy.

707
00:48:06,494 --> 00:48:09,112
She has us selling Kroehner caskets!

708
00:48:09,855 --> 00:48:11,649
Wow. She's good.

709
00:48:12,009 --> 00:48:14,706
Well, I guess we can at least help out Rico now.

710
00:48:15,133 --> 00:48:17,255
Yeah, that's a good idea.

711
00:48:17,275 --> 00:48:20,305
Then we go under, and he's out of work,
and he can't afford to pay us back.

712
00:48:20,306 --> 00:48:22,381
Which won't matter
because we won't exist anymore.

713
00:48:22,382 --> 00:48:25,407
David, we just saved 20000 $.

714
00:48:25,408 --> 00:48:29,138
We didn't save 20000 $ !
We just didn't spend it!

715
00:48:29,239 --> 00:48:31,434
Actually, we just lost 1600 $

716
00:48:31,435 --> 00:48:36,640
because we had to give the Langmeads the Haven 4 for 10500,
thank you very much!

717
00:48:45,262 --> 00:48:47,793
Honey, of course I love the house,

718
00:48:47,794 --> 00:48:50,444
but, believe me,
they are never gonna give us the money.

719
00:48:50,445 --> 00:48:52,331
You love the house, though.

720
00:48:52,643 --> 00:48:54,901
We just have to keep on looking, baby.

721
00:48:54,902 --> 00:48:58,505
No, we don't. I went to the realtor this morning,
and we got the house!

722
00:48:58,506 --> 00:49:02,241
I wrote a check for the down payment,
and now Julio can have his own room!

723
00:49:02,242 --> 00:49:06,054
What? Where did you get the money? What do you mean?

724
00:49:06,155 --> 00:49:09,017
Okay, don't be mad.

725
00:49:18,480 --> 00:49:22,058
You went behind my back and asked your sister for the money?
Are you crazy?

726
00:49:22,059 --> 00:49:26,235
- Rico, I wasn't about to lose that house.
- I provide for this family, NOT HER!

727
00:49:26,236 --> 00:49:27,923
I've gone 8 to 10 hours a day

728
00:49:27,924 --> 00:49:30,140
missing my kids
to get us what we need.

729
00:49:30,141 --> 00:49:31,500
I DON'T NEED HER FUCKING HANDOUTS!

730
00:49:31,501 --> 00:49:35,245
Please, I don't want to hear
any machismo bullshit today!

731
00:49:37,591 --> 00:49:40,174
What did you say to me?

732
00:49:43,755 --> 00:49:45,294
Baby,...

733
00:49:46,164 --> 00:49:48,259
we have a house.

734
00:49:48,460 --> 00:49:50,693
It's our first house.

735
00:49:51,094 --> 00:49:53,232
